comments.body:
@lstocchi I won't be able to fix https://github.com/containers/podman/issues/27597 right away. My brute force attempts to run tests as a normal user in the CI VM (windows server) have failed. I am trying to provision the VM on AWS to debug what's wrong but it will take time. And, even if we solve that, we still need to discuss if we can switch between users that have different roles (admin/hyvervadmin/unprivileged) in the same test. My goal for now is to run the WSL and installation tests as a normal user.

Apart from that we may still add tests to verify the start and stop of a legacy VM (created with a 5.7 client) but I would do that in a separate PR.

I looked at the code and did some tests locally and LGTM. I have added the label `No New Tests` to trigger the CI: a couple of tests are failing, but they look flakes, I will keep an eye on them.
